      <title>Denmark Strait</title>
      <link>https://malmans2.github.io/project/denmark-strait/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://malmans2.github.io/project/denmark-strait/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Denmark Strait is a channel located between Iceland and Greenland. Although the Strait is quite narrow, it plays a key role in the global climate system. The water masses that pass through Denmark Strait contribute significantly to the redistribution of heat between the poles and the equator.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Several currents interact with each other and with the seafloor in Denmark Strait. We can disentangle different pathways by seeding particles in our model. This animation shows how the temperature of water particles changes during their journey:&lt;br /&gt;

